<seg id=1> American Ambassador to China called on adopting a constructive policy to China </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, New York, 6 March by Zhou Xisheng In his speech on the Lunch Meeting of National Sino-American Relationship Committee in New York, American Ambassador to China, Shamger, called on America to adopt a strategic, stable and constructive policy to China, and to iron out differences between China via frankly and overall dialogues. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Shamger Pointed out that America should face China's rising on the international stage. No matter whether in this century or the next century, America should consider that improving the stable and healthy relationship with China was a great chance of American foreign policy. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> As far as China's humanity and property right protection of knowledge were concerned, the ambassador pointed out that China had made great progress. </seg>
<seg id=5> He believed that the freedom and democracy that Chinese people were enjoying were beyond compare. China had taken active and cooperative attitude in protecting property right of knowledge, to which America should not turn a blind eye. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> Shamger also suggested that after China joined WTO, America should cancel the annual discussion on according China most-favored-nation treatment, and should accord China most-favored-nation treatment forever. </seg>
<seg id=7> He pointed out that annual American Congress's discussion on this was actually harmful to America itself. American businessmen lost their confidence in investment in China, which affected American's employment chances. </seg>
</p>
